12 A JOINT RESOLUTION OF THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
13 MONTANA URGING UNIVERSITY SYSTEM SUPPORT FOR COLLEGIATE SHOOTING SPORTS IN THE
14 MONTANA UNIVERSITY SYSTEM.
15
16 WHEREAS, Montana has a long and honorable tradition of appropriate and constitutionally recognized
17 firearms use; and
18 WHEREAS, firearms and shooting are a common ingredient of contemporary life in Montana; and
19 WHEREAS, shooting sports are acceptable competitive activities throughout the world and in the
20 Olympics; and
21 WHEREAS, shooting sports are not recognized in the Montana University System as intermural, club,
22 or intercollegiate sports; and
23 WHEREAS, Montana produces an unusual number of excellent competitive shooters who accept
24 shooting scholarships at out-of-state colleges and universities because no shooting sports programs or
25 scholarships are available in the Montana University System; and
26 WHEREAS, shooting sports in Montana currently enjoy a safety record that cannot be matched by
27 most other organized sports; and
28 WHEREAS, shooting sports include a variety of activities, such as trap, skeet, sporting clays,
