1 smallbore, air rifle, air pistol, biathlon, pentathlon, practical pistol, precision rifle, and archery; and
2 WHEREAS, shooting sports are an area of competition in which the units of the Montana University
3 System can compete on equal footing with other institutions of higher education; and
4 WHEREAS, studies demonstrate that students involved in shooting competition also excel
5 academically; and
6 WHEREAS, shooting sports are an area of competition that promotes excellence and meaningful
7 participation, regardless of size, experience, sex, race, or even some physical disadvantages.
8
9 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF
10 THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11 (1) That the Montana Legislature encourages the Board of Regents and the units of the Montana
12 University System to adopt and facilitate shooting sports competitions as collegiate sports.
13 (2) That the Montana Legislature encourages the units of the Montana University System to utilize
14 university resources and to also partner with nonuniversity personnel and entities to facilitate shooting sports
15 competitions as collegiate sports.
16 (3) That the Montana Legislature encourages the units of the Montana University System to
17 develop endowments and offer scholarships for enrolled students competing in shooting sports.
18 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Secretary of State send a copy of this resolution to each
19 member of the Board of Regents and to the leaders of all public colleges and universities in Montana.
